div1.p:
In Justice's Court, Seattle Precinct, King County, Washington Territory, before N. SODERBERG, Justice of the Peace.
TERRITORY OF WASHINGTON, Plaintiff. vs. William J Tobias, Defendant. Commitment.

United States of America, Territory of Washington. County of King. ss.
To H. G. Thornton, Constable of said Precinct, or to any Constable of said County, and to the Kepper of the County Jail of said County, Greeting:
Whereas, At a Justice's Court held this day at the office of the undersigned, in the City of Seattle, in the said County, before the undersigned, a Justice of the Peace of said County, defendeant was admitted to bail in the sum of One Thousand Dollars, and has failed to furnish said bail.
And Wheras, Said cause has been temporarily continued ten days to await requisition from the Governor of Pa these are therefore to commadn you, the said Constable, forthwith to convery and deliver the said defendant to the said Keeper, and you the said Keeper are hereby commanded to receive said defendant into your custody in the said Jail, and him there safely keep subject to the orders of this Court, or, until he be thence discharged by due course of law.
Given under my hadn this 20th day of Sept 1889 Claudius M Rivers Justice of the Peace, Seattle Precinct, King County, W. T.

Commitment.
In Justice's Court, Seattle Precinct, King County, W. T.
Territory of Washington vs. William J. Tobias
Filed Sept 20th day of 1889 1888 C. M. Rivers Justice of the Peace.
